### Phase 3: Aggregator Upgrades

#### [MODIFY] [aggregator.py](file:///d:/Ed-!/backend/app/services/job_scraper/aggregator.py)

**3a. Per-Query Caching**
```python
# Before: Single cache key
_CACHE: dict = {"jobs": [], "cached_at": 0.0}

# After: Per-query cache buckets
_CACHE: dict[str, dict] = {}  # {"software": {"jobs": [...], "cached_at": 123.0}, ...}
CACHE_TTL = 60 * 60  # 60 minutes (up from 30)
MAX_CACHE_BUCKETS = 10  # LRU eviction
```

**3b. Per-Source Rate Limiting**
- Track last-call timestamps per scraper
- Enforce minimum intervals: Remotive (6h), others (10min)
- Prevents ToS violations on rate-limited APIs

**3c. Scraper Health Tracking**
```python
_HEALTH: dict[str, dict] = {}
# Example: {"remoteok": {"last_success": 123.0, "last_count": 45, "last_error": None, "consecutive_failures": 0}}
```
- Track success/failure/count per scraper per refresh cycle
- Expose via new API endpoint `/opportunities/health`

**3d. Better Deduplication**
- Use fuzzy matching (Levenshtein distance) on titles instead of just `title[:40]`
- Normalize company names (strip Inc, Ltd, etc.)
- Prefer listings with more data (salary > no salary, description > no description)

